---
import Layout from "../../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import "../../../css/services.css";
---

<Layout
  title="Web Design & Development | GeneralSoft UAE"
  description="Professional web design and development services in the UAE. We create responsive, SEO-optimized websites and web applications that drive business growth."
  path="/services/web-design/"
  image="/img/og-web.jpg"
>
  <section class="service-content" id="web-services">
    <div class="service-section" style="margin-top: 120px;">
      <h2 class="service-title">Web Design & Development</h2>
      <p>
        Your website is often the first interaction potential customers have with your business. At GeneralSoft, 
        we design and develop websites that make a lasting impression — combining stunning visual design with 
        robust technical performance. Based in the UAE, we serve businesses across the region with web solutions 
        that drive engagement and conversions.
      </p>
      <p>
        From simple brochure websites to complex web applications and e-commerce platforms, our team delivers 
        responsive, fast-loading, and SEO-optimized websites that work flawlessly across all devices and browsers.
      </p>

      <h3>Our Web Services</h3>
      <div class="features-grid">
        <div class="feature-box">
          <h4>Website Design</h4>
          <p>Custom website design with modern UI/UX principles, responsive layouts, and brand-aligned visual identity.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-box">
          <h4>Web Application Development</h4>
          <p>Complex web applications with interactive features, user authentication, dashboards, and real-time functionality.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-box">
          <h4>E-Commerce Solutions</h4>
          <p>Online stores with secure payment processing, inventory management, and seamless shopping experiences.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-box">
          <h4>SEO & Performance</h4>
          <p>Search engine optimization, performance optimization, and analytics integration to maximize your online presence.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h3>Our Web Technology Stack</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Frontend: React, Next.js, Astro, Vue.js, Angular</li>
        <li>Styling: Tailwind CSS, SCSS, CSS-in-JS</li>
        <li>Backend: Node.js, Python, PHP, .NET</li>
        <li>CMS: WordPress, Strapi, Sanity, Headless CMS</li>
        <li>Hosting: AWS, Vercel, Netlify, cPanel</li>
      </ul>

      <!-- Projects Proof Section -->
      <div class="projects-proof">
        <h3>Proven Web Delivery — Projects Completed</h3>
        <p>
          Our web portfolio spans e-commerce platforms, university portals,
          and corporate websites built for performance and scale.
        </p>

        <div class="project-card">
          <h4>Website Development — GeneralSoft RAKEZ</h4>
          <div class="project-meta">
            <span class="date">Jan 2025 – Jan 2025</span>
            <span class="role">Web Developer</span>
          </div>
          <p>
            Designed and developed the GeneralSoft corporate website using
            modern web technologies. Built with a focus on performance,
            bilingual support (English/Arabic), and lead generation. The site
            showcases our full range of services with a clean, professional
            design optimized for the UAE market.
          </p>
          <div class="tech-tags">
            <span class="tech-tag">HTML</span>
            <span class="tech-tag">CSS</span>
            <span class="tech-tag">JS</span>
            <span class="tech-tag">Astro</span>
            <span class="tech-tag">Responsive Design</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="project-card">
          <h4>E-Commerce Solutions — Retail Website Components</h4>
          <div class="project-meta">
            <span class="date">Oct 2000 – Jan 2001</span>
            <span class="role">Designer & Developer</span>
          </div>
          <p>
            Built website components for a retail e-commerce platform. Developed
            systems to convert supplier feeds into XML, update retail catalogs
            from supplier data, and validate catalogs prior to web publishing.
            The solution automated the entire product lifecycle from supplier
            ingestion to customer-facing display.
          </p>
          <div class="tech-tags">
            <span class="tech-tag">JSP</span>
            <span class="tech-tag">Java</span>
            <span class="tech-tag">PL/SQL</span>
            <span class="tech-tag">XML</span>
            <span class="tech-tag">Perl</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="project-card">
          <h4>University Portal — California State University</h4>
          <div class="project-meta">
            <span class="date">Feb 2001 – Apr 2001</span>
            <span class="role">Architect & Developer</span>
          </div>
          <p>
            Developed web portal components for California State University
            (CSU) enabling student registration, enrollment, course management,
            instructor administration, online teaching material publishing, and
            customer care. Built with JSP, Java, and PL/SQL.
          </p>
          <div class="tech-tags">
            <span class="tech-tag">JSP</span>
            <span class="tech-tag">Java</span>
            <span class="tech-tag">PL/SQL</span>
            <span class="tech-tag">Web Portal</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="project-card">
          <h4>Web 2.0 & PDA — Realty Industry Application</h4>
          <div class="project-meta">
            <span class="date">Sep 2007 – Dec 2007</span>
            <span class="role">Architect & Lead Developer</span>
          </div>
          <p>
            Built a shrink-wrap web application for the European realty industry
            enabling landlords to upload real-estate inventory data from PDAs
            and provide customer service via a Web 2.0 site. BizTalk served as
            the process manager for license management and contract
            documentation. Used GIS for assigning property inspections to
            inspectors.
          </p>
          <div class="tech-tags">
            <span class="tech-tag">ASP.NET</span>
            <span class="tech-tag">AJAX</span>
            <span class="tech-tag">Silverlight</span>
            <span class="tech-tag">BizTalk</span>
            <span class="tech-tag">GIS</span>
            <span class="tech-tag">Compact Framework</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="faq-section">

    <div class="container">
      <div class="faq-container">
        <h2 class="section-title">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
        <p class="section-subtitle">Common questions about our web design and development services.</p>
        <div class="faq-list">
          <details>
            <summary>How long does it take to build a website?</summary>
            <p>A standard business website typically takes 4–8 weeks. More complex web applications can take 8–16 weeks depending on features and requirements.</p>
          </details>
          <details>
            <summary>Do you offer website maintenance?</summary>
            <p>Yes. We provide ongoing maintenance packages including content updates, security patches, performance monitoring, and technical support.</p>
          </details>
          <details>
            <summary>Will my website be mobile-friendly?</summary>
            <p>Absolutely. All our websites are built with a mobile-first approach, ensuring they look and perform beautifully on smartphones, tablets, and desktops.</p>
          </details>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="contact" id="contact">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="contact-content">
        <h2>Create Your Digital Presence</h2>
        <p>Ready to build a website that stands out? Contact our web design team to get started.</p>
        <div class="contact-info">
          <div class="contact-item">
            <div class="contact-item-icon">🌐</div><strong>Website</strong><a href="https://generalsoft.ae">generalsoft.ae</a>
          </div>
          <div class="contact-item">
            <a href="/contact/"><div class="contact-item-icon">📧</div><strong>Contact Us</strong><br />Get in touch</a>
          </div>
          <div class="contact-item">
            <div class="contact-item-icon">📍</div><strong>Location</strong><span>Ras Al Khaimah</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
